but ironically not Martha Stewart.

254
00:09:59,737 --> 00:10:02,122
So dig up whatever you can

255
00:10:02,227 --> 00:10:06,019
and remember, photocopies are not admissible as memories.

256
00:10:06,121 --> 00:10:09,775
Uh, sir, I'm going to have to go or our old family storage unit in Reseda.

257
00:10:09,887 --> 00:10:10,692
No problem.

258
00:10:10,808 --> 00:10:13,048
We can arrange for a helicopter to take you there right now.

259
00:10:13,161 --> 00:10:17,020
Wow, this is the best free scrapbooking class I've ever taken.

260
00:10:17,137 --> 00:10:20,196
Meanwhile Lindsay and Lucille were at a spa in the desert

261
00:10:20,302 --> 00:10:23,280
avoiding both rehab and their depositions.

262
00:10:23,390 --> 00:10:26,718
Four saunas, three steam baths, Olympic sized pool

263
00:10:26,820 --> 00:10:29,335
and you're telling me there's no alcohol?

264
00:10:29,432 --> 00:10:32,221
What the hell are we supposed to do for two days.

265
00:10:32,322 --> 00:10:34,909
I could take the top off this grape juice and maybe by morning...

266
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,970
Oh, for God's sake, Lindsay, grow up.

267
00:10:37,075 --> 00:10:38,590
You're 40 years old.

268
00:10:38,693 --> 00:10:39,790
Thirty-five.

269
00:10:39,917 --> 00:10:41,619
Well, maybe this will be nice.

270
00:10:42,024 --> 00:10:45,851
We can talk... and connect a little.

271
00:10:48,498 --> 00:10:51,474
- I must have a Xanax.
- I'll go score some weed from the staff.

272
00:10:51,821 --> 00:10:54,500
And Michael and Buster checked out of the hospital.

273
00:10:54,598 --> 00:10:56,749
I can't believe they wouldn't even give me a wheelchair ride.

274
00:10:56,859 --> 00:10:59,850
We're going to be sitting on a plane for 18 hours to Iraq.

275
00:10:59,962 --> 00:11:01,856
Yeah, I should definitely get one for the airport.

276
00:11:02,097 --> 00:11:03,357
You're going to Iraq?

277
00:11:03,463 --> 00:11:05,791
Yes, I'm going to save my brother.

278
00:11:05,884 --> 00:11:08,660
Oh, so you are brave after all.

279
00:11:08,837 --> 00:11:11,069
Fighting for your brother.

280
00:11:11,170 --> 00:11:13,895
Oh, Buster, you're such a ( bleep ).

281
00:11:14,006 --> 00:11:14,826
That means she likes you.

282
00:11:14,943 --> 00:11:15,424
Oh.

283
00:11:15,531 --> 00:11:16,705
It's more than like.

284
00:11:16,823 --> 00:11:19,004
I'd give anything to have you stay here.

285
00:11:19,142 --> 00:11:21,774
Well, then I will stay here. I was scared to go anyway.

286
00:11:22,210 --> 00:11:23,173
Faker!

287
00:11:23,286 --> 00:11:24,779
I knew you were no good!

288
00:11:24,903 --> 00:11:27,260
Than I shall go-- to forget you.

289
00:11:27,368 --> 00:11:29,041
Oh, Buster, don't go.

290
00:11:29,148 --> 00:11:30,245
I don't want to go.

291
00:11:30,498 --> 00:11:32,662
I'm going to save everybody a lot of trouble and say that we are going.

292
00:11:32,752 --> 00:11:33,989
He is going. Come on, here we go.

293
00:11:34,095 --> 00:11:38,772
When I miss your lips, I'll put a fig in my mouth and think of you.

294
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,079
They have figs over there, right?

295
00:11:42,238 --> 00:11:43,660
I'll wait for you.

296
00:11:44,181 --> 00:11:45,108
What's this?

297
00:11:45,244 --> 00:11:48,518
Cabdriver said he went into a coma as soon as they pulled up to the hospital.

298
00:11:48,639 --> 00:11:51,330
Oh, what a brave man.

299
00:11:51,508 --> 00:11:56,082
And soon the Bluth boys found themselves in a strange land.

300
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:04,108
What did he say? Where are we?

301
00:12:04,209 --> 00:12:05,820
He said he's taking surface streets to LAX

302
00:12:05,917 --> 00:12:08,397
because the freeway's backed up all the way to Knott's Berry Farm.

303
00:12:08,505 --> 00:12:11,838
George Michael meanwhile got ahold of Maeby's address book

304
00:12:11,952 --> 00:12:15,555
to invite all of her friends to her Sweet 16.

305
00:12:15,665 --> 00:12:19,219
He did however, decide against some guests he found threatening.

306
00:12:19,330 --> 00:12:21,553
I don't think Steve Holt has to come to this.

307
00:12:21,798 --> 00:12:24,507
And yet he did invite Mickey Rourke.

308
00:12:24,629 --> 00:12:27,437
And the guys finally did get to Iraq.

309
00:12:27,558 --> 00:12:30,033
But Buster's Arabic was a little rusty

310
00:12:30,131 --> 00:12:34,336
and instead of a cab he hired them the only rickshaw in Baghdad.

311
00:12:34,446 --> 00:12:36,747
So you ready for Operation Hot Brother?

312
00:12:36,953 --> 00:12:38,220
I'm not ready to call it that.

313
00:12:38,323 --> 00:12:42,835
And they arrived at the prison the Americans were training Iraqis to run.

314
00:12:43,203 --> 00:12:44,556
What did you forget?

315
00:12:45,047 --> 00:12:46,757
Walk them through the...?

316
00:12:46,845 --> 00:12:47,513
The what?

317
00:12:47,599 --> 00:12:48,766
The metal detector.

318
00:12:48,871 --> 00:12:50,707
That's okay. Try again.

319
00:12:50,820 --> 00:12:52,038
My God, you came!

320
00:12:52,152 --> 00:12:53,034
Okay, okay.

321
00:12:53,132 --> 00:12:54,540
Oh, I missed you, Michael!

322
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,775
All right.

323
00:12:56,382 --> 00:12:58,371
Or should I say robot.

324
00:12:58,477 --> 00:12:59,612
What, 'cause I'm not crying?

325
00:12:59,719 --> 00:13:01,924
Maybe you don't have enough RAM to understand this, Michael,

326
00:13:02,003 --> 00:13:04,869
but there's such a thing as brotherly love.

327
00:13:05,163 --> 00:13:07,008
What's he doing here? I thought he was in a coma.

328
00:13:07,105 --> 00:13:09,030
I was trying to prove to this nurse that I'm brave.

329
00:13:09,139 --> 00:13:11,829
I need to get a picture of me with the insurgent. I can send it on my phone.

330
00:13:12,051 --> 00:13:13,850
Why were you arrested by the Americans?

331
00:13:13,947 --> 00:13:15,932
I was just doing a little off-mission street magic.

332
00:13:16,027 --> 00:13:17,209
Trying to make a few dinars.

333
00:13:17,317 --> 00:13:24,988
And that is why Jesus was often referred to as the King of Kings.

334
00:13:25,368 --> 00:13:26,248
Queens.

335
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:27,773
The King of Queens.

336
00:13:27,958 --> 00:13:32,065
And now I would like to behold one of the late great Jesus' biggest illusions,

337
00:13:32,165 --> 00:13:33,677
The Burning Bush.

338
00:13:33,833 --> 00:13:38,449
Burn Bush, burn Bush, burn Bush, burn Bush...

339
00:13:38,528 --> 00:13:41,282
But soon the security forces arrived to suppress

340
00:13:41,380 --> 00:13:44,955
what now appeared to be an anti-American demonstration.

341
00:13:45,057 --> 00:13:46,960
Burn Bush, burn Bush...

342
00:13:47,044 --> 00:13:49,176
That's okay, use your foot.

343
00:13:49,277 --> 00:13:50,448
The thigh bruises.

344
00:13:50,544 --> 00:13:51,283
What doesn't?

345
00:13:51,375 --> 00:13:52,176
Try again.

346
00:13:52,283 --> 00:13:53,906
So you weren't doing anything for Dad?

347
00:13:54,005 --> 00:13:56,906
Well, Dad... I mean, he had said if I happened to be in the neighborhood

348
00:13:56,975 --> 00:13:59,993
of Sadr City or Momoon would I mind torching a couple model homes.

349
00:14:00,080 --> 00:14:02,999
But you know, Dad's just trying to keep information out of the hands of the Iraqis.

350
00:14:03,116 --> 00:14:05,028
I have a feeling he was trying to keep information

351
00:14:05,121 --> 00:14:06,726
out of the hands of the federal marshals.

352
00:14:06,827 --> 00:14:09,036
I'm going to go collect my things and say my good-byes.

353
00:14:09,132 --> 00:14:10,028
You guys check me out of here.

354
00:14:10,129 --> 00:14:13,141
Gob, you're an enemy combatant. It's not going to be that easy.

355
00:14:13,232 --> 00:14:17,857
I mean, I'll talk to them, but you might want to prepare for a long stay.

356
00:14:24,182 --> 00:14:26,187
Oh, shoot, I forgot to say good-bye to Yusef.

357
00:14:26,279 --> 00:14:28,487
That was a lot easier than I expected.

358
00:14:28,589 --> 00:14:29,917
Almost too easy.

359
00:14:30,033 --> 00:14:31,638
Hey, why aren't we going to the airport?

360
00:14:31,746 --> 00:14:34,088
Well, I want to go check out this house Dad asked you to burn down.

361
00:14:34,179 --> 00:14:36,342
See what he's hiding. I think that's it, sir.

362
00:14:38,906 --> 00:14:40,330
Buster, this guy speaks English.

363
00:14:40,418 --> 00:14:42,264
Oh, no. I swallowed a moth.

364
00:14:42,365 --> 00:14:43,805
I'm sorry it took so long,

365
00:14:43,904 --> 00:14:47,410
but the Cheney Expressway was backed up all the way to Halliburton Drive.

366
00:14:49,593 --> 00:14:51,491
Let's  see what all the mystery is about, huh?

367
00:14:51,607 --> 00:14:56,510
And that's when Michael found someone the U.S. government had been able to depose.

368
00:14:56,599 --> 00:14:57,689
Hello.

369
00:14:58,993 --> 00:15:00,905
Take my picture! Take my picture!

370
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:07,228
Michael was in Iraq when he came across a familiar face.

371
00:15:07,345 --> 00:15:08,816
Are you, uh...?

372
00:15:08,911 --> 00:15:10,486
Saddam Hussein.

373
00:15:11,108 --> 00:15:12,752
Look-alike.

374
00:15:13,311 --> 00:15:14,296
Who are you?

375
00:15:14,427 --> 00:15:18,228
I'm Michael Bluth. These are my brothers, Buster and Gob Bluth.

376
00:15:18,329 --> 00:15:21,117
Bluth? Is he here to fix the air-conditioning?

377
00:15:21,213 --> 00:15:23,750
Are you both Saddam Hussein look-alikes?

378
00:15:23,856 --> 00:15:26,359
Hardly. Invite them in.

379
00:15:26,473 --> 00:15:29,464
I am behaving like an Uday look-alike.

380
00:15:29,569 --> 00:15:31,310
Come on in. Come on in, guys.

381
00:15:31,416 --> 00:15:34,571
I'd always heard that there were Saddam Hussein look-alikes.

382
00:15:34,670 --> 00:15:37,464
I guess I'm just a little surprised to see you all living here

383
00:15:37,577 --> 00:15:40,411
in one house that looks so similar to ours.

384
00:15:40,537 --> 00:15:42,701
Scar on that one dude's forehead's got to be a problem.

385
00:15:42,795 --> 00:15:45,622
That's Achmed. Never stops watching the trial.

386
00:15:45,742 --> 00:15:48,050
We are all following it pretty closely.

387
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:50,436
I understand. They put this guy away you guys are out of a job, huh?

388
00:15:50,544 --> 00:15:53,884
Yes, and we wanted to keep the house for just one more season.

389
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,835
I have a baby on the way.

390
00:15:55,954 --> 00:15:57,852
I do a better Saddam than this guy.

391
00:15:57,967 --> 00:15:59,447
My Saddam would show his teeth.

392
00:15:59,554 --> 00:16:01,413
Yes, to chew the scenery.

393
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:03,918
And so Michael decided the least he could do

394
00:16:04,013 --> 00:16:05,973
was take a look at the air-conditioning.

395
00:16:06,089 --> 00:16:08,261
But before he did, he decided to see

396
00:16:08,356 --> 00:16:12,203
if there was a secret room in this model home as well.

397
00:16:12,856 --> 00:16:16,429
And that's when Michael discovered the bombshell.

398
00:16:17,547 --> 00:16:18,317
Buster!

399
00:16:18,429 --> 00:16:20,772
And back at the American model home,

400
00:16:20,881 --> 00:16:24,062
none of the invitees had shown up for Maeby's party.

401
00:16:24,169 --> 00:16:25,698
Surprise.

402
00:16:25,803 --> 00:16:26,960
Yeah, that's what I figured.

403
00:16:27,082 --> 00:16:30,780
So, did you send one of these to everyone in my address book?

404
00:16:30,878 --> 00:16:32,327
Yeah. I'm really sorry they didn't come.

405
00:16:32,423 --> 00:16:33,190
I don't know what happened.

406
00:16:33,287 --> 00:16:33,831
I do.

407
00:16:33,944 --> 00:16:35,523
They found out I was 16.

408
00:16:35,628 --> 00:16:38,678
And a lot of us just didn't want to drive down to Orange County.

409
00:16:38,772 --> 00:16:39,515
What are you talking about?

410
00:16:39,634 --> 00:16:41,673
This cost me my job, George Michael.

411
00:16:41,787 --> 00:16:43,535
I was a studio executive.

412
00:16:43,633 --> 00:16:44,879
I made movies.

413
00:16:44,988 --> 00:16:47,035
Well, is that why you've been so stressed out all the time?

414
00:16:47,131 --> 00:16:48,233
Have I been?

415
00:16:48,348 --> 00:16:49,617
You know what, I'm a kid.

416
00:16:49,715 --> 00:16:51,191
I'm going to start acting like one.

417
00:16:51,299 --> 00:16:52,294
What, you're going to drink?

418
00:16:52,391 --> 00:16:53,827
Do you want to join me?

419
00:16:54,078 --> 00:16:56,071
Well, I guess if you can run a studio.

420
00:16:56,175 --> 00:17:00,031
But they didn't know it was the fake wine from Gob's magic show.

421
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:00,644
It's good.

422
00:17:00,754 --> 00:17:02,396
And back in Iraq...

423
00:17:02,501 --> 00:17:03,236
What is this?

424
00:17:03,340 --> 00:17:05,389
Looks like a mid-range nuclear warhead.

425
00:17:05,506 --> 00:17:09,168
Has a range capacity of 4,000 to 5,000 nautical miles.

426
00:17:09,275 --> 00:17:11,855
You've got a pretty sophisticated knowledge of this technology.

427
00:17:11,956 --> 00:17:14,497
My God, it makes me want to have an ice-cream cone.

428
00:17:14,596 --> 00:17:15,938
Doesn't this make you want to have an ice-cream cone?

429
00:17:16,037 --> 00:17:16,947
It does make me want to have an ice-cream cone.

430
00:17:17,057 --> 00:17:20,133
You'll have plenty of time for ice cream in prison.

431
00:17:20,237 --> 00:17:22,343
Ice cream sandwiches.

432
00:17:22,449 --> 00:17:23,766
CIA undercover.

433
00:17:23,877 --> 00:17:27,336
CIA, of course. This explains why it was so easy to get you out of prison.

434
00:17:27,438 --> 00:17:31,695
I knew that if he got out he would lead us right to whatever your dad was hiding.

435
00:17:31,797 --> 00:17:34,597
They'd even created opportunities for this to happen.

436
00:17:34,699 --> 00:17:36,392
Get in the cell, stupid.

437
00:17:36,547 --> 00:17:39,957
You... you... you're the one who didn't even shut the door.

438
00:17:40,708 --> 00:17:41,707
Come on!

439
00:17:41,824 --> 00:17:44,556
Yeah, you guys can run this place without us.

440
00:17:44,692 --> 00:17:48,105
As soon as you stop dropping your keys.

441
00:17:48,371 --> 00:17:49,320
Come on!

442
00:17:49,427 --> 00:17:52,603
They'd even staged something called an honor marathon

443
00:17:52,703 --> 00:17:55,209
they thought he was sure to take advantage of.

444
00:17:55,332 --> 00:17:55,842
Come on.

445
00:17:55,950 --> 00:17:58,825
We've been looking for WMD's for years.

446
00:17:58,921 --> 00:18:00,501
WMD's?

447
00:18:00,984 --> 00:18:03,804
This thing is as fake as Achmed's mustache.

448
00:18:03,865 --> 00:18:04,393
See?

449
00:18:04,497 --> 00:18:06,161
Yeah, look, it's a Homefill.

450
00:18:06,266 --> 00:18:09,635
It's the company that makes the fake stuff we fill the model homes with.

451
00:18:09,960 --> 00:18:11,022
What the hell?

452
00:18:11,133 --> 00:18:12,739
What is that, a recording device?

453
00:18:12,849 --> 00:18:13,839
This is our stuff.

454
00:18:13,942 --> 00:18:15,608
Okay, I got to call this in.

455
00:18:16,488 --> 00:18:17,487
Buster, please.

456
00:18:17,588 --> 00:18:18,521
Baker.

457
00:18:19,209 --> 00:18:21,054
No, it doesn't sound like CIA East.

458
00:18:21,154 --> 00:18:22,761
I'll check with CIA West.

459
00:18:22,955 --> 00:18:25,120
Did we bug a house in Mamoon?

460
00:18:26,669 --> 00:18:28,590
Yeah. We got some guy named George Bluth

461
00:18:28,696 --> 00:18:30,930
to build houses down there so we could wire them.

462
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:33,534
Look, I'm Uncle Buster.

463
00:18:34,610 --> 00:18:36,710
I'm sorry no one from the family came.

464
00:18:36,816 --> 00:18:39,034
Sometimes I wish I wasn't even part of the family.

465
00:18:39,128 --> 00:18:42,175
No, don't... no... I've never wanted to say this...

466
00:18:42,315 --> 00:18:45,950
but you might not even be related to us.

467
00:18:46,005 --> 00:18:46,739
No.

468
00:18:46,854 --> 00:18:48,109
'Cause Gangee once said to me,

469
00:18:48,220 --> 00:18:50,590
your mom might not have ever even been pregnant with you.

470
00:18:50,699 --> 00:18:53,131
Okay, now you're just saying that to make me feel better.

471
00:18:53,245 --> 00:18:56,210
No, I'm... I wouldn't.

472
00:18:56,835 --> 00:18:58,379
Everyone still loves you.

473
00:18:59,417 --> 00:19:00,911
Some more than others.

474
00:19:01,020 --> 00:19:03,212
And perhaps it was the fake wine,

475
00:19:03,327 --> 00:19:07,485
but that was the night George Michael and Maeby went to second base.

476
00:19:09,784 --> 00:19:12,349
So my dad was a patsy?

477
00:19:12,808 --> 00:19:16,334
We call them "unintentional operations victims," but yes.

478
00:19:16,443 --> 00:19:18,966
We ran the whole operation through a British building company.

479
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:20,492
And they contacted my dad for the plans.

480
00:19:20,604 --> 00:19:23,196
I can't believe it-- after all of that he wasn't lying.

481
00:19:23,316 --> 00:19:26,772
Look, we feel terrible because this is really our mistake.

482
00:19:27,030 --> 00:19:30,079
But I'm afraid I'm going to have to take you guys out.

483
00:19:30,189 --> 00:19:31,170
Take us out?

484
00:19:31,296 --> 00:19:31,778
Where?

485
00:19:31,895 --> 00:19:33,469
I could really go for some Italian.

486
00:19:33,577 --> 00:19:35,362
There is an Olive Garden in Mamoon.

487
00:19:35,479 --> 00:19:37,517
I think he means to shoot you in the head.

488
00:19:37,646 --> 00:19:41,075
But please, at least let him look at the air-conditioning.

489
00:19:41,188 --> 00:19:44,314
Sir, if you're worried about us talking, we will not say a word.

490
00:19:44,438 --> 00:19:47,244
Well, don't be mad, but I have been sending the pictures from my cell phone to my friend.

491
00:19:47,351 --> 00:19:49,740
He doesn't not know what he's saying...

492
00:19:50,728 --> 00:19:51,870
You have?

493
00:19:52,041 --> 00:19:56,771
Well, who knows who she sent them to?

494
00:19:59,122 --> 00:20:01,660
Yeah. Yeah, I get it.

495
00:20:03,030 --> 00:20:05,140
Looks like you are a hero, Buster.

496
00:20:05,366 --> 00:20:06,783
We both are.

497
00:20:06,895 --> 00:20:07,564
Well...

498
00:20:07,675 --> 00:20:09,294
Okay, looks like you got us.

499
00:20:09,407 --> 00:20:11,828
What can the U.S. government do for you?

500
00:20:11,982 --> 00:20:14,905
We're going to need some business class tickets home.

501
00:20:15,003 --> 00:20:18,783
And direct flights. None of this stopping in Phoenix bull ( bleep ).

502
00:20:18,891 --> 00:20:21,160
And more importantly, maybe we can drop

503
00:20:21,251 --> 00:20:23,316
some of these treason charges against my father.

504
00:20:23,435 --> 00:20:27,478
And I do believe there was some mention of some ice cream.

505
00:20:27,605 --> 00:20:31,131
And so, with Operation Hot Brother a success,

506
00:20:31,234 --> 00:20:33,540
Our American heroes left Iraq.

507
00:20:33,656 --> 00:20:35,743
